data.title: Has Debra Messing moved on from 10-year marriage? Will and Grace actress linked to new co-star
data.meta_description: Messing is said to be in a new romance with Will Chase, 41, who appears alongside her in the upcoming NBC musical drama, Smash.
data.text:
New romance? Debra Messing and her new Smash co-star Will Chase, pictured here in November, are said to be dating

Will and Grace star Debra Messing has been romantically linked to her new co-star - just a week after announcing the end of her 10-year marriage.

The actress, 43, and TV producer husband Daniel Zelman, 44, who have a 7-year-old son, Roman, split earlier this year.

Now Messing is said to be in a new romance with Will Chase, 41, who appears alongside her in the upcoming NBC musical drama, Smash.

'Debra and Will have been together for about six weeks,' a source tells America's Us Weekly.

'She's completely smitten with him.'

But the insider insists: 'Will didn't break up Debra and Daniel. It was over before she met Will.'

Chase is said to have recently left his wife of two years, actress Stephanie Gibson.

He has two children, who are almost teenagers, from a previous marriage.

Amicable: The actress and Daniel Zelman, pictured here with their child Roman, remain 'committed to raising their son as a family'

Messing is still living under the same roof as her estranged husband under 'very amicable terms'.

A spokesperson said last week that the decision to split 'was mutual, and they remain supportive of one another and committed to raising their son as a family.'

The former couple even attended Bette Midler's Halloween gala together in October however it is unclear if they will spend the holidays together as a family.

The pair married in 2000 after meeting as students at New York University.

Debra and Will's new series Smash will debut in February.
